name: #001 - Panthotenic acid (B5)
description:
Class: Body

Availability: Common

Known as vitamin B5, is water-soluble and all animals require it to synthetize coenzyme A, essential for methabolism. Its name derives from the Greek 'pantos', meaning "from everywhere", as minimally, at least small quantities of pantothenic acid are found in nearly every food.

>> The vibration and movement of these molecules are performed by calculus of simulation called Molecular Mechanics where each molecule optimizes its geometry trying to get the lower energy possible.
